article.headline: King, Harris help North Carolina Central edge Delaware State 69-66
article.description: — Po'Boigh King had 22 points, Ja'Darius Harris scored 21 and North Carolina Central held off Delaware State 69-66 on Monday night.
article.linkText: King, Harris help North Carolina Central edge Delaware State 69-66
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- — Po'Boigh King had 22 points, Ja'Darius Harris scored 21 and North Carolina Central held off Delaware State 69-66 on Monday night. King added five rebounds for the Eagles (12-8, 4-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Harris hit two 3-pointers. Fred Cleveland Jr. totaled 11 points and six rebounds. The Hornets (10-11, 3-2) were led in scoring by Jevin Muniz, who finished with 24 points. Khyrie Staten added 11 points and two steals. Wesley Oba finished with seven points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
